data.title: Student Academic Honors - Fall 2023
data.text:
Congratulations to the 3,456 ACC students who earned academic honors during the Fall 2023 semester, including 1,004 on the Dean’s List (3.50-3.74 term GPA), 268 on the Vice President’s List (3.75-3.99 term GPA), and 2,184 on the President’s List (4.0 term GPA). Students must successfully complete a minimum of six credit hours during the semester to be eligible for academic honors.

ACC provides innovative and responsive educational and economic opportunities in an accessible, inclusive environment. ACC offers both in-person and online classes, serving students throughout Arapahoe County, Douglas County and south metro Denver. ACC has seven academic pathways for students to explore, connect and succeed, as well as guaranteed transfer programs to all four-year public universities in Colorado.
